    <abstract>
      <t>This specification defines the "IPv6 over the TSCH mode of IEEE 802.15.4" (6TiSCH) Minimal Scheduling Function (MSF).  This Scheduling Function describes both the behavior of a node when joining the network and how the communication schedule is managed in a distributed fashion.  MSF is built upon the 6TiSCH Operation Sublayer Protocol (6P) and the minimal security framework for 6TiSCH.
	 </t>
